                <p>
                  Chat is the primary interface for interacting with the model in DartBoard.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Unlike standard chat systems, conversations here are memory-aware and context-controlled, giving you
                  direct oversight of what information the model can access at any moment. You can attach memories, pin or
                  unpin them to control prompt injection, switch operational modes, and observe how context changes affect
                  responses in real time.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Beyond live interaction, Chat functions as a persistent working environment. You can save and edit
                  messages as reusable memories, search across sessions by keyword, and navigate conversations using
                  time-based buckets. The goal is not simply to talk to an AI, but to run structured, intentional
                  interactions where context is explicit, controllable, and never lost to scrollback.
                </p>
              </InfoCard>
            )}
            
            {selectedTab === "archive" && (
              <InfoCard title="Archive">
                <p>
                  Archive is the retrieval layer for DartBoard. It lets you search across past sessions by keyword, jump
                  through time-bucketed slices, and quickly re-open the exact window of context where an idea happened.
                </p>
                <p>
                  It&apos;s built for recovering decisions, notes, and threads that would otherwise be lost to scrollback.
                  Think of it as your personal search engine for everything you&apos;ve discussed with the model.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Navigate by date, filter by topic, or search specific phrases to find exactly when and where a
                  conversation took place. Archive ensures your AI interactions become a searchable knowledge base rather
                  than ephemeral chat history.
                </p>
              </InfoCard>
